*Estonian: [[:et:raba|raba]] (1)
*French: [[:fr:marais|marais]] ''m'', [[:fr:bruyère|bruyère]] ''f''
*German: [[:de:Moor|Moor]] ''n'' (1)

===Etymology 3===
imp. & p. p. [[Moored]]; p. pr. & vb. n. [[Mooring]].<BR>
Prob. fr. D. [[marren]] to tie, fasten, or moor a ship. See [[Mar]].

====Verb====
'''to moor'''
#''(intransitive)'' To [[cast]] [[anchor]] or become [[fasten]]ed.
#''(transitive)'' (''Nautical'') To fix or secure, as a vessel, in a particular  place by casting anchor, or by fastening with cables or chains; as, ''the vessel was moored in the stream''; ''they  moored the boat to the wharf''.
#''(transitive)'' To [[secure]], or [[fix]] [[firm]]ly.

